Unity Editor

Live Capture Packages
The Unity Live Capture package is a powerful tool that allows for real-time performance capture and recording within the Unity Editor.

The package consists of two major features: Virtual Camera and Face Capture, bothing utilizing the power of IOS ARKIT to help artists and creators create immersive camera movements and natural facial animation.
Virtual Camera Capture and record camera motion through an iPhone or iPad as if you were physically in the Unity Scene.
Face Capture Capture and record face movements through an iOS device and apply them on a character in the Unity Scene.

Synchronization Genlock and synchronize all connected devices to get frame accuracy across the timeline and the captured dataset.

My Responsibilities
As the lead designer on this project, my role involved collaborating closely with the product manager, researchers, and owners to pinpoint the business objectives, understand user needs, and identify pain points. I reimagined the workflow for both products and their integration within the Unity editor and app store, streamlining the user experience. Working hand in hand with developers, we executed the refined user flow, ensuring seamless functionality and transition across multiple platforms, including Windows, macOS, iOS, and Android, to enhance user engagement and satisfaction.
Case Studies
01 Virtual Camera System Redesign
Problem : The Virtual Camera is a complex system invovles simutanous operation between the Unity editor and the IOS app. In the editor, multiple windows, game objects and components are present, which create major obstacles and confusion points for the user to sucessfully create shots using their virtual camera.
